<div style="height:120px;width:120px;border:1px solid #ccc;font:16px/26px Georgia, Garamond, Serif;overflow:auto;">
As you can see, once there's enough text in this box, the box will grow scroll bars... that's why we call it a scroll box! You could also place an image into the scroll box.
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="scroll-box col-md-6">
    <h3>Rides I've requested: </h3>
    {{#if userRides}}
    {{#each userRides}}
    <p>Rider: {{this.rider.firstName}}</p>
    <p>Driver: {{this.driver.firstName}}</p>
    <p>Status: {{this.status}}</p>
    <p>Destination: {{this.destination.formatted_address}}</p>
    {{/each}}
    {{else}}
    <a href="/app" style="color: purple;">Click here to request a new ride.</a>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <div class="scroll-box col-md-6">
    <h3>Rides I've accepted: </h3>
    {{#if userDrives}}
    {{#each userDrives}}
    <p>Rider: {{this.rider.firstName}}</p>
    <p>Driver: {{this.driver.firstName}}</p>
    <p>Status: {{this.status}}</p>
    <p>Destination: {{this.destination.formatted_address}}</p>
    {{/each}}
    {{else}}
    <a href="/app" style="color: purple;">Click here to browse rides requested by other drivers.</a>
    {{/if}}
  </div>
</div>

<div class="userInfo" style="margin-bottom: 20px">
  <h2>Hello {{user.username}}!</h2>
  <p id="firstName">{{user.firstName}}</p>
  <p id="lastName">{{user.lastName}}</p>
  <a href="/users/edit">
    <!-- Edit or delete user profile here -->
    <!-- <button id="editBtn">Edit User</button> -->
  </a>
  <a href="/logout">
    <button>Logout</button>
  </a>
</div>
